claim.claim-text:
A pocket hole jig tool (210), comprising:
a base (214) including a work-piece side support surface (46) and a work-piece end support surface (48);
a drill guide support (218) slidably mounted to said base (214) and adapted for movement toward and away from said work-piece side support surface (46) of said base;
a guide block (220) movably mounted relative to said drill guide support (218);
at least one drill guide bushing (222, 224) mounted to said guide block (220), wherein said guide block (220) is movably supported by at least one slide surface (234) of said drill guide support (218); and
a drill guide locking mechanism adapted to lockingly engage said guide block (220) relative to said drill guide support (218) characterized in that:
said drill guide locking mechanism includes a cam member (286) movable from a disengaged to an engaged position relative to a cam follower assembly (274) that, upon movement of said cam member (286) to said engaged position, applies a clamping force against a surface (234) of said drill guide support (218) to engage said guide block (220) in a fixed position relative to said drill guide support (218); and wherein said drill guide locking mechanism includes a first cam (280) a second cam (280) and a third cam (288) each movable from a disengaged position to an engaged position relative to a respective first cam follower mechanism (274), a second cam follower mechanism (274) and a third cam follower mechanism (292) that, upon movement of said first cam, said second cam and said third cam to said engaged position, each apply a clamping force against a surface (234) of said drill guide support (218) to engage said guide block (220) in a fixed position relative to said drill guide support (218).

